docs.lead_paragraph: The Cabinet today approved an exchange control decree raising the value of the Uruguayan peso to 7.60 to the pound sterling, or approximately 1.54 to the dollar. (The New York quotation yesterday was 53 cents for the peso, or about 1.89 pesos to the dollar.)
